HEADWORD: kinetic
<hw>ki*net"ic</hw> <pr>(k⟦icr⟧*n⟦ecr⟧t"⟦icr⟧k ⟦or⟧
k⟦isl⟧*n⟦ecr⟧t"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>kinhtiko`s</grk>, from <grk>kinei^n</grk> to move.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Moving or causing motion; motory; active, as
opposed to latent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Kinetic energy</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Energy</er>,
